title: Australia Households Debt To GDP
description: Households Debt in Australia decreased to 118.40 percent of GDP in the first quarter of 2022 from 119 percent of GDP in the fourth quarter of 2021. Households Debt to GDP in Australia averaged 76.20 percent of GDP from 1977 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 124.10 percent of GDP in the third quarter of 2016 and a record low of 34.20 percent of GDP in the fourth quarter of 1977. This page provides - Australia Households Debt To Gdp- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Bank for International Settlements
